Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Server not responding

Solution: Check if PHP server is running with ps aux | grep php. Restart with php -S localhost:8080 &
Issue: Permission denied reading files

Solution: Ensure test files exist and are readable. Use ls -la to check permissions.
Issue: JSON parsing errors

Solution: Verify XML syntax is correct. Use xmllint --noout file.xml to validate XML.
Issue: Python scripts not working

Solution: Install required packages: pip3 install requests. Check Python version with python3 --version.
Conclusion
This lab demonstrated XML External Entity (XXE) vulnerabilities in web APIs. You learned to identify vulnerable XML parsers, exploit XXE to access sensitive files, automate attacks with Python, and implement proper defenses. Key takeaways:

Always disable external entity processing in XML parsers
Use secure parser configurations and input validation
Implement allowlists for acceptable XML content
Regular security testing helps identify XXE vulnerabilities
Defense-in-depth approach: combine multiple security controls
XXE remains a critical vulnerability in modern applications. Apply these defensive techniques in production systems to prevent data exposure and server-side request forgery attacks.
